The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 9th as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. The proclamation pays tribute to former prisoners of war who have faced challenges and dangers to protect the country's freedom. It acknowledges the sacrifices made by these individuals and their families, highlighting their courage and selfless sacrifice. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe this day by honoring service members, veterans, and all American prisoners of war. It also encourages government officials and organizations to hold appropriate ceremonies and activities to recognize these individuals.